Transformation_Mapping_rule: Fixed % fee rate| e.g. 0.02563 would be 2.563%.     For display purpose| the percentage figure is rounded up to 2 decimal places. In the example| it will be 2.57%.     In the case of an investment management fee of a portfolio| it can have multiple fixed percentage fee profiles. (It cannot be in sliding scale). Hence this element is added up for the same portfolio and same master book kind and then rounded up to 2 decimal places before displaying on UI.     In the case of a portfolio management fee| it can have one fee profile only. Hence there is no need to add this element for the same portfolio and same master book kind. However| the value is still rounded up to 2 decimal places before displaying on UI.
